				\begin{document}$${\sigma }_{0}=27.84\,{{{\rm{kg}}}}\,{{{\rm{m}}}}^{-3}$$\end{document}σ0=27.84kgm−3 (Fig. 2b, which on average is around 2000m). At this relatively dense level, the depth-space AMOC has little reduction (i.e. 0.8 Sv around 2000m) (Fig. 2e); instead, the reduction of the horizontal circulation contribution (4.9 Sv) dominates the total density-space AMOC reduction of 5.7 Sv (Fig. 2b, e).

